# Chrome DevTools MCP - Browser Inspection

**When to use:**
- Debugging frontend issues
- Inspecting DOM structure
- Testing HTMX interactions
- Verifying React Island rendering
- Performance analysis
- Network request debugging

**How to use:**
```typescript
// Navigate to page
mcp_chrome-devtools_navigate_page({ url: "http://localhost:8000" })

// Take snapshot (better than screenshot)
mcp_chrome-devtools_take_snapshot({ verbose: false })

// Interact with elements
mcp_chrome-devtools_click({ uid: "element-uid" })
mcp_chrome-devtools_fill({ uid: "input-uid", value: "text" })

// Check console/network
mcp_chrome-devtools_list_console_messages({ types: ["error"] })
mcp_chrome-devtools_list_network_requests()

// Performance analysis
mcp_chrome-devtools_performance_start_trace({ reload: true, autoStop: true })
```

**Why:**
- Real browser environment testing
- Debug HTMX swaps
- Verify React Island hydration
- Check network requests
- Performance profiling

**Use cases:**
- Debugging HTMX template issues
- Verifying React Island props/data
- Testing WebSocket connections
- Performance optimization

**Prefer over:**
- Screenshots (use snapshots for accessibility tree)
- Manual browser testing (automated inspection)
